title: SQL/sql.sql
ATM8 Seed List Creator
content:
seedInfo = {}
seeds = {}
seedsCounter = 0
detector = peripheral.wrap("bottom")
dataPath = "data/seeds/"
blackbox = ""
isBlackbox = false
startedTimestamp = os.date("%d-%m-%y.%H-%M-%S")
	--25*6
	
function addLog(newLogLine)
	if isBlackbox then
		blackbox = blackbox .. os.date() .. newLogLine .. "\n"
	end
end

function detect()
	addLog("detect()")
	if turtle.inspectDown() then
		return detector.list()
	else
		return false
	end
end

function init()
	addLog("init()")
	if !fs.exist(dataPath) then
		fs.makeDir(dataPath)
	end
end

function move(direction)
	addLog("move(" .. direction .. ")")
	fuelLevel = turtle.getFuelLevel()
	if fuelLevel == 0 then
		refueled = turtle.refuel(1)
		while refueled == false do
			print("Need fuel")
			refueled = waitForFuel()
		end
	end
	if direction == "forward"
		turtle.forward()
	end
end

function waitForFuel()
	addLog("waitForFuel()")
	sleep(1)
	return turtle.refuel(1) or turtle.getFuelLevel() > 0
end
--seed = {name, id, mod, count}
--[[
turtle.inspectDown()
bool (isDetected)
table
	state table
	name "botanypots:red_terracotta..."
	tags table
		
tags
]]

function turnAround(direction)
	addLog("turnAround(" .. direction .. ")")
	if(direction == "left") then
		turtle.turnLeft()
		move("forward)
		turtle.turnLeft()
	elseif (direction == "right") then
		turtle.turnRight()
		move("forward)
		turtle.turnRight()
	end
end

function getAllSeeds(numberOfLines,length)
	addLog("getAllSeeds(" .. numberOfLines .. ", ".. length .. ")")
	for i=1,numberOfLines,1 do
		getSeedLine(length)
		if math.fmod(i,2) == 1 then
			turnAround("left")
		else
			turnAround("right")
		end
	end
	if math.fmod(numberOfLines,2) == 1 then
		turtle.turnLeft()
		turtle.turnLeft()
	end
	turtle.turnLeft()
	for i=1,numberOfLines,1 do
		move("forward")
	end
	turtle.turnRight();
end

function getSeedLine(length)
	addLog("getSeedLine(" .. length .. ")")
	for i=1,length,1 do
		currItems = detect()
		addSeed(currItems)
		move("forward")
	end
end

function addSeed(items)
	addLog("addSeed(" .. items .. ")")
	for key,value in pairs(items) do
		if(seeds[key] != nil) then
			seeds[key] = 1
		else
			seeds[key] = seeds[key] + 1
		end
	end
	seedsCounter = seedsCounter + 1
end

function getInputInt(msg)
	x,y = term.getCursorPos()
	repeat
		write(msg)
		input = read()
		inputNumber = tonumber(input)
		if inputNumber != nil then
			if inputNumer - math.floor(inputNumber) == 0 then
				return inputNumber
			end
		end
		term.setCursorPos(1,y)
		term.clearLine()
	until false
end

function getSeedsAsString(seeds)
	ret = ""
	for key,value in pairs(seeds) do
		ret = ret .. value .. "\n"
	end
	return ret
end

function main()
	print("started")
	addLog("main()")
	
	length = getInputInt("length of row: ")
	rows = getInputInt("number of rows: ")
	getAllSeeds(rows, length)
	currFile = fs.open( dataPath + "sum-" .. startedTimestamp, "w")
	currFile.write(getSeedsAsString(seeds))
	
	if isBlackbox then
		currLogFile = fs.open( dataPath + "sum-log-" .. startedTimestamp, "w")
		currLogFile.write(blackbox)
	end

	print("finished")
end
--fs.open( dataPath + "seedx","w")
main()

title: Execute Perform
monitorar_bau
content:
local qtd = 0

rednet.open("right")

local chest = peripheral.wrap("left")
local monitor = peripheral.wrap("monitor_1")

while true do
    lista = chest.list()
    range = #lista

    qtd = 0
    for i = 1, range, 1 do
        qtd = qtd + (lista[i].count)
    end

    print(qtd)

    monitor.clear()
    monitor.setCursorPos(4, 3)
    monitor.write(qtd .. " Batatas")

    sleep(420)
end

title: BWR - Changelog 02/09/23
content:
Spy
+ Spy sprint with speed boost should match your boosted speed
Fists of Steel
- Fixed reduced overheal building extra ubercharge
~ Fix only works outside of spawn
Dalokohs Bar
+ Reverted recharge time to 10s (was 15s)
- Fixed max overheal increase and uber building bugs
Requisite fixing of bugs, former one to make using spy sprint with the RTR consistent, latter two to avoid unintentionally building uber too fast with a pocketed heavy. Dalokohs recharge was reverted as compensation as it seemed underwhelming without exploits.

Jarate
+ Increased cooldown reduction from extinguishing teameates to -33% (was -20%)
+ Fixed cooldown reduction to be the intended -8s on kill (was -4s)
Mad Milk
+ Increased cooldown reduction from extinguishing teameates to -33% (was -20%)
Gas Passer
+ Increased cooldown reduction from extinguishing teameates to -33% (was -20%)
- Removed cleaning of debuffs in gas cloud
Making the supportive usage of jar weapons more rewarding with the slower recharge. In addition, the gas passer's cloud was not use terribly much for support due to cost of using it and rarity one might need it.

Warrior's Spirit
- Added: No Random Crits
The added damage made the addition of a crit combo somewhat overkill

Backburner
+ Added +33% airblast push force to self
Due to the higher cost of the airblast making its utility more costly, it was felt it should have it's mobility improved to aid in flanking with it without relying on a secondary.

Buffalo Steak Sandvich
- Removed reduction in push force taken from damage
- Removed reduction in airblast vulnerability
Both the speed and knockback made a steak heavy almost unstoppable by normal means, thus reintroducing some counter felt necessary to keep it in check.

Righteous Bison
+ Increased damage bonus to +200%
- Reverted clip size penalty to -33%
Reverting it's clip felt necessary due to its penetration and spammable nature. It's damage was buffed slightly to make up for this, making it more comparable to the shotgun in mid-range.

Conniver's Kunai
+ Increased max health drain restored at 3/s (was 1.5/s)
The regeneration appeared to be far too punishing, requiring over 10 seconds to recover from a single stab. This buff should make it only require at most 20 seconds for your max HP to recover from a chainstab.

Reserve Shooter
+ Removed clip size penalty
- Reduced accuracy bonus to 15% (was 25%)
Panic Attack
- Removed accuracy bonus (was 15% more)
Meant to cut back on excess statistics on items.

Killing Gloves of Boxing
~ Changed On-Kill: gain 100% crits until your next attack or rev up, and 3 second thereafter
+ Crit boost lasts until you start your next rev up or attack
- Crit duration reduced from 5 seconds to 3 seconds (not counting rev time)
With the higher bar to gaining crits, a buff was felt. These changes are meant to make transfering the crits to your next attack more reasonable for the heavy, while keeping the potential duration of crits more limited, particularly with the minigun.

Sharpened Volcano Fragment
- Reduced volcano effect's fire weakness to a +30% vulnerability (was mini-crits)
Given the number of pyro weapons that deal crits/mini-crits on burning enemies, it was felt giving a boost to damage would help prevent overlap and be a better pay-off.

Third Degree
~ Reverted damage link to targets connected by heal beams
+ Linked players includes targets connected through dispeners
+ Removed less healing from healers
Reverted to be more in-line with it's original theme, expanding its use against groups of enemies being healed. Due to the more limited usage, the healing downside was removed.

Quick-Fix
+ Removed ubercharge duration penalty
+ Blast Jump mirroring is toggleable with the RELOAD key
- Blast Jump mirroring makes medic take half the self-damage of their patient
- Reverted ubercharge bonus to +10% (was +33%)
The faster build speed seemed oppressive against other ubers, particularly on limited team sizes. To help with the reverting of its build speed, it's duration was restored, making sharing with teammates even more rewarding. In addition, the blast jumping mirroring was made less free to use but more in the user's control.

--Wireless Redstone Control Listener

local output = "back"
local sender_id = 5
local wireless_modem = peripheral.find("modem", function(name, modem)
    return modem.isWireless()
end)
rednet.open(peripheral.getName(wireless_modem))

print("Listening")
while true do
	id, message = rednet.receive()
    if id == sender_id then
        if message == "New" then
			redstone.setAnalogOutput(output, 1)
			os.sleep(1)
			redstone.setAnalogOutput(output, 0)
			print("Received")
		else
			--do nothing
		end
	else
		--do nothing
	end
end

-- Variaveis
local isBlock, data
local isPotato, pot

-- Funções
function inspect_potato()
    isPotato, pot = turtle.inspect()

    if (pot.state.age == 7) then
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.place()
    end
end

function deepslate_harvester()
    turtle.turnLeft()

    for i = 0, 7, 1 do
        inspect_potato()
        turtle.turnLeft()
        turtle.turnLeft()
        inspect_potato()
        turtle.turnRight()

        if (i < 7) then
            turtle.forward()
            turtle.turnRight()
        end

        isBlock, data = turtle.inspect()

        if (data.name == "minecraft:glass") then
            turtle.dropDown()
            sleep(600)
        end

    end
end

function glass_harvester()
    turtle.turnRight()

    for i = 0, 7, 1 do
        inspect_potato()
        turtle.turnRight()
        turtle.turnRight()
        inspect_potato()
        turtle.turnLeft()

        if (i < 7) then
            turtle.forward()
            turtle.turnLeft()
        end

        isBlock, data = turtle.inspect()

        if (data.name == "minecraft:deepslate_tiles") then
            turtle.dropDown()
            sleep(600)
        end

    end
end

-- Loop
while true do
    -- Verifica qual bloco a turtle está olhando
    isBlock, data = turtle.inspect()

    -- Se estiver olhando stone, faça:
    if (data.name == "minecraft:deepslate_tiles") then
        deepslate_harvester()
    end

    -- Se estiver olhando glass, faça:
    if (data.name == "minecraft:glass") then
        glass_harvester()
    end
end

    // Parcours des caractères du texte à afficher

        const letter = T.charAt(j);
        // Détermination de la plage de caractères correspondant à la lettre
        const alphaBeginning = letter.toUpperCase() === letter ? 'A' : 'a';
        const alphaEnding = letter.toUpperCase() === letter ? 'Z' : 'z';
        let start = 0;
        if (letter < alphaBeginning || letter > alphaEnding) {
            start = ((alphaEnding.charCodeAt(0) - alphaBeginning.charCodeAt(0)) + 1) * L;

// Lecture de la largeur d'une lettre en art ASCII (L) et de sa hauteur (H)
fscanf(STDIN, "%d", $L);
fscanf(STDIN, "%d", $H);

// Lecture de la ligne de texte à afficher en art ASCII (T)
$T = stream_get_line(STDIN, 256 + 1, "\n");

// Conversion du texte en majuscules pour simplifier les correspondances en art ASCII
$T = strtoupper($T);

// Lecture des caractères de l'alphabet en art ASCII
for ($i = 0; $i < $H; $i++)
{
    $ROW = stream_get_line(STDIN, 1024 + 1, "\n");
    $output = '';

    // Parcours des caractères du texte à afficher
    for ($j = 0; $j < strlen($T); $j++) {
        $letter = $T[$j];

        // Détermination de la plage de caractères correspondant à la lettre
        $alphaBeginning = ctype_upper($letter) ? 'A' : 'a';
        $alphaEnding = ctype_upper($letter) ? 'Z' : 'z';
        $start = 0;

        if (ord($letter) < ord($alphaBeginning) || ord($letter) > ord($alphaEnding)) {
            $start = ((ord($alphaEnding) - ord($alphaBeginning)) + 1) * $L;
        } else {
            $start = (ord($letter) - ord($alphaBeginning)) * $L;
        }

        // Ajout de la partie correspondante de la ligne ROW à la sortie
        $output .= substr($ROW, $start, $L);
    }

    // Affichage de la ligne
    echo($output . "\n");
}

                cache[item]["displayName"] = fallback.displayName:match("^%s*%[?(.-)%]?%s*$")
            end

            -- monkey-patching a bug in rsBridge
            if storage ~= nil and storage.amount ~= 0 then
                storageCount = storage.amount
                if storageCount == getCraftingMultiplier(item) and recipe ~= nil then
                    storageCount = 0
                end
            end

            cache[item]["inStorage"] = storageCount
            cache[item]["available"] = storageCount
            cache[item]["needed"] = 0
        end
        return cache[item]
    end

    function getCraftingMultiplier(item)
        local itemData = loadItemData(item)
        if itemData.recipe == nil then
            return 0
        end
        for _, result in pairs(itemData.recipe.outputs) do
            if result.name == item then
                return result.amount
            end
        end
        return 0
    end

    function simplifyRecipeIngredients(recipe)
        local ingredients = {}
        for _, input in pairs(recipe.inputs) do
            input = input[1]
            if input ~= nil and input.amount ~= nil and input.name ~= "minecraft:air" then
                if ingredients[input.name] == nil then
                    ingredients[input.name] = {
                        count = 0,
                        fallback = input
                    }
                end
                ingredients[input.name].count = ingredients[input.name].count + input.amount
            end
        end
        return ingredients
    end

    function mark(item, amount, fallback)
        local itemData = loadItemData(item, fallback)
        itemData.available = itemData.available - amount
        itemData.needed = itemData.needed + amount

        if itemData.available < 0 then
            local multiplier = getCraftingMultiplier(item)
            if multiplier == 0 then
                return
            end

            local craftingCount = math.ceil(-itemData.available / multiplier)

            for input, inputData in pairs(simplifyRecipeIngredients(itemData.recipe)) do
                mark(input, inputData.count * craftingCount, inputData.fallback)
            end
        end
    end

    mark(targetItem, 1)
    local result = {}
    for item, itemData in pairs(cache) do
        if itemData.recipe == nil and itemData.inStorage < itemData.needed then
            result[item] = {
                inStorage = itemData.inStorage,
                needed = itemData.needed,
                displayName = itemData.displayName
            }
        end
    end
    return result
end

function displayIngredients(ingredients)
    monitor.clear()
    monitor.setCursorPos(1, 1)
    for _, itemData in pairs(ingredients) do
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.orange)
        monitor.write(itemData.displayName .. ": ")
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.lightBlue)
        monitor.write(itemData.inStorage .. "")
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.blue)
        monitor.write("/" .. itemData.needed)

        _, cursorPos = monitor.getCursorPos()
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, cursorPos + 1)
    end
end

function startClock()
    while (true) do
        ingredients = getIngredients("allthetweaks:pulsating_black_hole")
        displayIngredients(ingredients)
        sleep(60)
    end
end
startClock()

                tool:Activate() -- activate the tool

                    local v = p[i].Character
                    if v and v:FindFirstChild("Humanoid") and v.Humanoid.Health > 0 and v:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart") and game.Players.LocalPlayer:DistanceFromCharacter(v.HumanoidRootPart.Position) <= 15 then -- check if the player is alive, has a humanoid root part, and is within 15 units of distance
                        for i,v in next, v:GetChildren() do -- loop through all the parts of the player's character
                            if v:IsA("BasePart") then -- check if the part is a base part
                                firetouchinterest(tool.Handle,v,0) -- fire touch interest with the tool's handle and the part
                                firetouchinterest(tool.Handle,v,1)
                            end
                        end
                    end
                end
            end
        end)
    end
end)

local localPlayer = game:GetService("Players").LocalPlayer
local currentCamera = game:GetService("Workspace").CurrentCamera
local mouse = localPlayer:GetMouse()

local function getClosestPlayer()
    local closestPlayer = nil
    local shortestDistance = math.huge

    for i, v in pairs(game:GetService("Players"):GetPlayers()) do
        if v.Name ~= localPlayer.Name then -- check if the player is not the local player
            if v.Character and v.Character:FindFirstChild("Humanoid") and v.Character.Humanoid.Health ~= 0 and v.Character:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart") and v.Character:FindFirstChild("Head") then -- check if the player has a character, a humanoid, a humanoid root part, and a head
                if not v.Character:FindFirstChildOfClass("ForceField") then -- check if the player does not have a force field
                    local ray = Ray.new(v.Character:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart").Position, Vector3.new(0,-100000,0)) -- create a ray from the player's humanoid root part to downwards
                    local Hit = game:GetService("Workspace"):FindPartOnRay(ray, v.Character) -- find the part that the ray hits

                    if Hit then -- check if the ray hit something
                        local magnitude = (v.Character.HumanoidRootPart.Position - localPlayer.Character.HumanoidRootPart.Position).magnitude -- calculate the distance between the player and the local player

                        if magnitude < shortestDistance then -- check if the distance is shorter than the previous shortest distance
                            closestPlayer = v -- update the closest player
                            shortestDistance = magnitude -- update the shortest distance
                        end
                    end         
                end
            end
        end
    end

    return closestPlayer -- return the closest player or nil if none found
end

local stateType = Enum.HumanoidStateType

local character = game.Players.LocalPlayer.Character
local humanoid = character:WaitForChild("Humanoid")

humanoid:SetStateEnabled(stateType.FallingDown, false) -- disable the falling down state
humanoid:SetStateEnabled(stateType.Ragdoll, false) -- disable the ragdoll state

while true do
    wait()
    spawn(function()
        local target = getClosestPlayer() -- get the closest player
        if game:GetService("Players").LocalPlayer.Character.PrimaryPart and target and i_said_right_foot_creep == true then -- check if the local player has a primary part, a target, and the variable is true
            local TargetPart = target.Character.HumanoidRootPart -- get the target's humanoid root part
            local Part = game.Players.LocalPlayer.Character.HumanoidRootPart -- get the local player's humanoid root part
            local RotateX, RotateY, RotateZ = 0, 0, 0

            Part.CFrame = CFrame.new(Part.Position, TargetPart.Position) * CFrame.Angles(math.rad(0), math.rad(25), math.rad(0)) -- set the part's CFrame to face the target's position with a 25 degree offset

            game:GetService("Players").LocalPlayer.Character.Humanoid:MoveTo(TargetPart.CFrame * Vector3.new(-3, 0, 0)) -- move to the target's position with a 3 unit offset
            if target.Character.Humanoid:GetState() == Enum.HumanoidStateType.Freefall then -- check if the target is in freefall state
                game.Players.LocalPlayer.Character.Humanoid.Jump = true -- make the local player jump
            end
        end
    end)
end

ssss.KeyDown:connect(function(key) -- connect a function to the key down event of the mouse

            game:GetService("Players").LocalPlayer.Character:FindFirstChildOfClass('Humanoid').AutoRotate  = true -- enable the auto rotate of the humanoid   
        end
    end
end)
